## Superseded from documentation-corpus-myrmidon-parallel-remediation

```yaml
name: documentation-corpus-myrmidon-parallel-remediation
description: "Myrmidon swarm pattern for remediating a large document corpus in parallel using isolated git worktree agents. Use when: (1) an unpublished research corpus contains change-note prose, correction-history blocks, or backward-compatibility text that must be deleted (not annotated), (2) defects span many files and must be fixed in parallel without file ownership collisions, (3) you need wave-based execution: parallel fixers → read-only verifier → merge. Includes citation-verification pass that web-fetches arXiv abstracts to catch fabricated numeric ranges, reversed-polarity claims, and paper-body figures misattributed as abstract-level."
category: documentation
date: 2026-04-20
version: "1.6.0"
user-invocable: false
verification: verified-local
history: documentation-corpus-myrmidon-parallel-remediation.history
tags: [myrmidon, swarm, parallel, corpus, remediation, worktree, wave-based, change-notes, unpublished, conflict-partitioning, citation-verification, arxiv-abstract-check]
```

Key content absorbed: WATCH/GO conflict-partitioning protocol, Wave A/B/C architecture
(parallel fixers → read-only verifier → narrow-patch merge), R1–R6 repair class taxonomy,
8-pass expanded scrub pattern list (literal-phrase / bibliography-suffix / semantic-judgment /
authorial-review / frontmatter-process-metadata / support-doc-changelog / citation-verification /
arithmetic-cross-check), mandatory Wave A post-completion verification (`merge-base --is-ancestor`),
`git apply --3way` conflict marker gate (`grep -rnE "^<<<<<<<"`), Wave B verdict uniqueness
check (per-section not per-file), dual-template verification gates (Standard §8 vs Thematic),
agent count by corpus size table, narrow-patch cherry-pick when worktree base diverged,
foreground-only for long-running agents (no run_in_background), fold R6 into WATCH-file agents,
`--amend` HEAD verification requirement, bibliography change-note sub-classes, fabricated
numeric range detection via arXiv WebFetch.

Sessions: ArchIdeas 39-file corpus across 5 runs (2026-04-18 through 2026-04-20), v1.0.0→v1.6.0.

